TY  - JOUR
AU  - De Angelis, David
AU  - Grinstein, Yaniv
T1  - Performance Terms in CEO Compensation Contracts*
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfu014
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 19
IS  - 2
SP  - 619
EP  - 651
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - In December 2006, the Securities and Exchange Commission issued new rules that require enhanced disclosure on how firms tie CEO compensation to performance. We use this new available data to study the terms of performance-based awards in CEO compensation contracts in S&amp;P 500 firms. We observe large variations in the choice of performance measures. Our evidence is consistent with predictions from optimal contracting theories: firms rely on performance measures that are more informative of CEO actions.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfu014
ER  - 



