T1  - Taxation, Transfer Income and Stock Market Participation*
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfu008
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 19
IS  - 2
SP  - 823
EP  - 863
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This article studies the impact of a redistributive tax system on consumption, portfolio decisions, and asset prices in a dynamic general equilibrium model. Poorer agents, which receive more in transfers than they pay in taxes, optimally reduce their exposure to equity, because the transfer income they receive is subject to stock market risk. This article thus provides a novel explanation for the low stock market participation rates of poorer investors.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfu008
ER  - 



